<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xml:id="tbxManager" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>tbxManager</refname>
        <refpurpose>open the GUI check-list of toolboxes</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Syntax</title>
        <synopsis>
tbxManager()
        </synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>Opens a scrollable check-list of the known toolboxes. Tick the ones to enable, then <emphasis>Apply</emphasis> (save the selection) or <emphasis>Apply &amp; Relaunch</emphasis> (save and restart the app so the checked toolboxes autoload immediately). The verified-on-macOS set is pre-ticked. Requires the Scilab desktop (STD mode).</para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
tbxManager();
]]></programlisting>
    </refsection>
